t: The*p Lord*s reigneth, he is clothed with majesty; the Lord*s is clothed with strength, wherewith he hath girded himself: the world also is stablished, that it cannot be moved.
Thy*p throne is established of old: thou art from everlasting.
The*p floods have lifted up, O Lord,*s the floods have lifted up their voice; the floods lift up their waves.
The*p Lord*s on high is mightier than the noise of many waters, yea, than the mighty waves of the sea.
Thy*p testimonies are very sure: holiness becometh thine house, O Lord,*s for ever.
